    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The metal interior of a coin. Especially in clad coins, the core is usually made of a lower-value metal (copper or bronze) covered by a higher-value metal (gold or silver).</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
